         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">6th June [189]4 ¶ editorial addition. ¶ Sir, ¶  ¶ I have the honor to inform you that His Excellency the Governor in Council has been pleased to retain your services as Government Botanist until the 3...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">94.06.06</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Charles Topp</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Y94/4140, unit 818, VPRS 3992/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style=""/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The text is taken from an unsigned letterpress copy.</p>
               </note>6th June [189]4<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">editorial addition.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have the honor to inform you that His Excellency the Governor in Council has been pleased to retain your services as Government Botanist until the 31st December 1894.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>For M's reply, see<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M to C. Topp, 8 June 1894.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>On 29 May 1894,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the Chief Secretary, J. Patterson,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>had<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>recommended to the Governor in Council the continued employment of M,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Government Astronomer<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Robert Ellery,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Government Statist, Henry Hayter. Approval was granted the same day. A certificate continuing the employment of these three<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>until 31 December 1894, dated 28 May,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>was signed by the members of the Public Service Board and and sent to the Premier (Y94/3972, unit 818, VPRS 3992/P,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Public Record Office, Victoria).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your obedient servant</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron Sir Ferdinand Von Mueller K.C.M.G.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Government Botanist.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c.<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c.</p>
